This paper is primarily focused on visualizing image representations, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (cs.LG), and discusses the limitations and potential improvements of these techniques (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses optimization methods to achieve its visualizations, which is a common topic in both neural networks and computer vision (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of its findings in multimedia analysis (cs.MM).
